    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix parameter order in add_ue_to_remove function calls\n\n### Summary\nThe `add_ue_to_remove` function in RRC eNB had an unconventional parameter order that made it prone to parameter swapping errors. The function signature was changed to follow a more conventional pattern (container, item, count) and all calls were updated accordingly.\n\nThis fix addresses the issue of \"incorrect argument order in function call swapping similarly-typed parameters downstream of function add_ue_to_remove\".\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: Updated function signature and all 7 calls to use proper parameter order\n- The function now follows the conventional pattern: container first, then item, then count\n- This makes it less likely for developers to accidentally swap the similarly-typed parameters\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, the function had parameters in an unconventional order which could lead to confusion when calling the function. The fix ensures all calls use the correct parameter order:\n`add_ue_to_remove(ue_to_be_removed, ue_context_p, removed_ue_count)`\n\n"
}